HEADWORD: Analogism
<hw>A*nal"o*gism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ course
of reasoning, fr. <?/ to think over, to calculate]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>an argument from the cause to the effect; an
<it>a priori</it> argument.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Investigation of things by the analogy they bear to
each other.</def> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Analogist</ent>⟦br⟧
